('c1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000023', 'b1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002', 23, 'multiple_choice', 'What were the objectives of the WZCS document? A) improve calibre of zoos world-wide B) identify zoos suitable for conservation C) provide funds for zoos in underdeveloped countries D) list endangered species of the world', 'B', 1),
('c1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000024', 'b1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002', 24, 'multiple_choice', 'Why does the writer refer to Robin Hill Adventure Park? A) to support the Isle of Wight local council B) to criticise the UK Zoo Licensing Act C) to illustrate a weakness in the WZCS document D) to exemplify standards in AAZPA zoos', 'C', 1),
('c1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000025', 'b1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002', 25, 'multiple_choice', 'What word best describes the writer''''s response to Colin Tudge''''s prediction? A) disbelieving B) impartial C) prejudiced D) accepting', 'A', 1),
('c1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000026', 'b1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002', 26, 'multiple_choice', 'Which THREE factors lead the writer to doubt the WZCS document? A) number of unregistered zoos B) lack of money in developing countries C) actions of Isle of Wight council D) failure to examine core zoo standards E) unrealistic aim given species saved to date F) policies of WZCS zoo managers', 'A', 1),
